Gemini free tier gave immediate limit: 0 quota errors on gemini-2.0-flash with a brand new API key. No clear guidance in the error about whether this is a model availability issue, a billing issue, or a provisioning delay. A developer hitting this cold would have no idea whether to wait, switch models, or add a credit card. Switched to Groq as a workaround — worked immediately with no configuration issues.

Dataset creation via SDK was straightforward, but there's no immediate feedback in the UI that examples were added successfully until you navigate to the dataset manually. A loading state or success confirmation in the UI would help new users confirm their SDK calls worked.

The Playground API key dialog is confusing. The layout shows what appears to be the key value at the top, then an unlabeled input field below it that turns out to be for the key name, not the key value itself. Spent several minutes trying to figure out why Start wouldn't run. The actual key input field isn't clearly labeled or visually distinct from the name field.